00:38:14,900 --> 00:38:17,560
videos of early playtest levels,

896
00:38:17,560 --> 00:38:19,861
but they're all on my website, ehilldesign.com.

897
00:38:19,861 --> 00:38:22,742
Basically just showing a bit of the block mesh process,

898
00:38:22,742 --> 00:38:25,462
the kinds of things that we do to walk the player through

899
00:38:25,462 --> 00:38:26,283
and have that playable prototype.

900
00:38:26,283 --> 00:38:29,163
But just as another example, looking at this,

901
00:38:29,163 --> 00:38:32,024
look at this mess, look at this scribble.

902
00:38:32,024 --> 00:38:34,965
This is an early storyboard for JoJo's Bizarre Adventure.

903
00:38:34,965 --> 00:38:36,785
The person behind this is like

904
00:38:36,785 --> 00:38:38,906
one of the best draftsmen alive.

905
00:38:38,906 --> 00:38:40,426
This guy's been in the Louvre.

